tables.description: The audit_checks table represents a record of regular audits performed across various sites. It stores information about the audit date, the auditor who conducted the audit, and the audit score obtained. This table is typically used in analytics and business workflows to track compliance and identify areas for improvement.

columns.description: The audit_pk column represents a unique identifier for each audit record. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the audit_checks table. This column is essential for tracking and linking audit records.

The site_fk column represents the foreign key that links each audit record to the corresponding site in the site_master table. It is an integer value that indicates the site where the audit was conducted. This column is used to track site-specific audit data.
The audit_dt column represents the date when the audit was conducted. It is a date value that provides a timestamp for each audit record. This column is used to track audit schedules and timelines.

The auditor column represents the name of the person who conducted the audit. It is a character varying value that stores the auditor's name. This column is used to track audit personnel and their roles.

The audit_score column represents the score obtained during the audit. It is an integer value that indicates the level of compliance or risk. This column is used to track audit results and identify areas for improvement.

tables.description: The event_log table captures significant events that occur within the organization, such as changes to staff roles or completion of training courses. It stores information about the event date, the staff member involved, and the category of the event. This table is crucial for auditing and tracking changes within the organization.

columns.description: The event_pk column represents a unique identifier for each event record. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the event_log table. This column is essential for tracking and linking event records.

The staff_fk column represents the foreign key that links each event record to the corresponding staff member in the staff table. It is an integer value that indicates the staff member involved in the event. This column is used to track staff-related events.
The event_dt column represents the date when the event occurred. It is a date value that provides a timestamp for each event record. This column is used to track event schedules and timelines.
The event_category column represents the category of the event. It is a character varying value that stores the event category. This column is used to track event types and their frequencies.

The risk_level column represents the level of risk associated with the event. It is an integer value that indicates the severity of the event. This column is used to track risk levels and identify potential threats.

tables.description: The learning_records table stores information about the training courses completed by staff members. It contains details about the course name, completion date, and the staff member's completion status. This table is used to track staff development and identify areas where additional training is required.

columns.description: The learning_pk column represents a unique identifier for each learning record. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the learning_records table. This column is essential for tracking and linking learning records.

The staff_fk column represents the foreign key that links each learning record to the corresponding staff member in the staff table. It is an integer value that indicates the staff member who completed the course. This column is used to track staff learning and development.

The course_name column represents the name of the course completed by the staff member. It is a character varying value that stores the course name. This column is used to track course titles and completion rates.

The course_dt column represents the date when the course was completed. It is a date value that provides a timestamp for each learning record. This column is used to track course completion dates and timelines.

The completion_status column represents the status of the course completion. It is a character varying value that stores the completion status. This column is used to track course completion rates and identify areas for improvement.

tables.description: The org_units table represents the organizational structure of the company, including departments, teams, and other units. It stores information about the unit title, site affiliation, and the unit head. This table is essential for understanding the company's organizational hierarchy and for making informed decisions about resource allocation.

columns.description: The unit_pk column represents a unique identifier for each organizational unit. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the org_units table. This column is essential for tracking and linking unit records.
The unit_title column represents the title of the organizational unit. It is a character varying value that stores the unit title. This column is used to track unit names and descriptions.

The site_fk column represents the foreign key that links each unit record to the corresponding site in the site_master table. It is an integer value that indicates the site where the unit is located. This column is used to track site-specific unit data.
The unit_head column represents the head of the organizational unit. It is a character varying value that stores the unit head's name. This column is used to track unit leadership and roles.

The created_on column represents the date when the unit was created. It is a timestamp value that provides a timestamp for each unit record. This column is used to track unit creation dates and timelines.

tables.description: The site_master table contains information about the company's sites, including their titles, locations, and creation dates. It provides a comprehensive view of the company's global presence and is used to track site-related data and metrics.

columns.description: The site_pk column represents a unique identifier for each site. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the site_master table. This column is essential for tracking and linking site records.
The site_title column represents the title of the site. It is a character varying value that stores the site title. This column is used to track site names and descriptions.
The nation column represents the nation where the site is located. It is a character varying value that stores the nation name. This column is used to track site locations and geographies.
The region column represents the region where the site is located. It is a character varying value that stores the region name. This column is used to track site locations and geographies.

The created_on column represents the date when the site was created. It is a timestamp value that provides a timestamp for each site record. This column is used to track site creation dates and timelines.

tables.description: The staff table stores information about the company's employees, including their full names, job roles, and unit affiliations. It also contains details about their joining dates and is used to track staff demographics and performance metrics.

columns.description: The staff_pk column represents a unique identifier for each staff member. It is an integer value that serves as a primary key for the staff table. This column is essential for tracking and linking staff records.

The staff_fullname column represents the full name of the staff member. It is a character varying value that stores the staff member's full name. This column is used to track staff demographics and contact information.

The unit_fk column represents the foreign key that links each staff member to the corresponding unit in the org_units table. It is an integer value that indicates the unit where the staff member is assigned. This column is used to track staff unit assignments.
The role_name column represents the job role of the staff member. It is a character varying value that stores the role name. This column is used to track staff roles and responsibilities.

The joining_date column represents the date when the staff member joined the organization. It is a date value that provides a timestamp for each staff record. This column is used to track staff joining dates and timelines.
